nl.fw.yapool

Class PrunedPool<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.fw.yapool.Pool<T>
      • nl.fw.yapool.BoundPool<T>
        • nl.fw.yapool.PrunedPool<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPool<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ObjectPool, SqlPool

    public class PrunedPool<T>
extends BoundPool<T>
    A BoundPool that can actively remove idled and expired resources from the pool (see prune()). To prune this pool regularly, register this pool using PoolPruner.add(PrunedPool) (an instance of PoolPruner is available via PoolPruner.getInstance()).
    Various actions can be taken when a resource idled/expired, see the various set-methods of this class. For additional debugging, consider the use of the LeaserAcquiredTrace listener.
    Author:
    fwiers

      • acquire

        public T acquire(long acquireTimeOutMs,
        long maxLeasedTimeMs)
        Calls BoundPool.acquire(long) but also validates the returned resource. If validation fails, the resource is evicted from the pool and BoundPool.acquire(long) is called again, if there is any acquire-time left.
        Parameters:
        maxLeasedTimeMs - if 0, lease time never exprires.
